posts.title: Vance / Cracker 2028

posts.raw_content:
Day by day it becomes more clear that our systems have become so bloated and corrupted that there’s no real separation of powers, governing hierarchy, or consistent enforcement of the structures that used to work. 

Local, state, and federal laws all conflict.. rogue judges and elected/unelected officials rule with absolute authority. Interest rates and inflation are determined by a select few, not reality of economic conditions. Everyone goes along with it. Sure there are occasional legal battles to fight back, but the outcomes have a narrow scope impact at best and isn’t based on facts, precedent, or laws.. it’s based on who and where a case is ruled on and whatever agenda they have. The game is being played where the rules don’t matter to the rulers and consequences are for the players.

So.. why do we continue to play? The will of the people gets ignored at all levels of govt. People have tried to change the path by focusing on the local level, but then the state overrides their local authority. People tried to make change by focusing on the state level, but then federal bodies override their state authority. We focused on the federal level, but all of a sudden local/state laws can override federal.. and judges can override federal, local, state, AND executive orders? Govt was designed to have clear scope of authority to prevent people on the other side of the country dictating what you can/can’t do in your state or city. Federal govt was designed to ONLY govern issues between states with differing laws. People in govt are not only overreaching their scope of authority, but the checks/balances selectively look the other way or act outside of their authority to bypass the system and exercise powers they don’t have. The levels of govt are now treated similar to the levels of courts, with the courts assuming executive authority. Local govt is now the lower courts.. anything state or federal can override.. and federal judges can bypass it all without a fight. And now the SC can ignore precedent and the executive branch to decide for themselves what’s law and how to interpret it.

Why do we continue to pretend that the govt as it is, is necessary? It’d be easier to revert to the model of government the founding fathers outlined and go from there rather than trying to fix the oversized convoluted mess it’s become. Politicians should be a thing of the past and govt should be handled like a business, where the people are the customers.. common sense and budget based on revenue. In the business world, more rules means more overhead and more frustrated customers which leads to decreased revenue. Govt should be no different. There needs to be consequences for their actions that the people don’t support. They should not be able to continue expanding by forcing everyone to pay the bill without any say in what their money is going towards.
